It is important to stress that in general the LPE growth process has been successfully treated as a thermodynamic process.[72] A thermodynamic analysis of Al incorporation in GaN toward the formation of AlGaN during MBE growth of nitride semiconductors under metal-rich conditions was presented by Hoke et al.[73] As discussed previously the active nitrogen dissolves in the liquid Ga in the surface of the film and incorporates in the GaN seed from the liquid phase. If simultaneously Al atoms arrive on the substrate, then the incorporation of Al is favored, if the Gibbs free energy at the growth temperature (ΔGT) of the reaction in Eq. (1) is negative. (1)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
